<aura:documentation>
    <aura:description>
    <div class="slds-m-top_large">
		<h4>Overview</h4>
		<p>The <code>&lt;c:PEG_ChatterGroups_CMP&gt;</code> component may be used in any type of
		Lightning page and is available directly in the App Builder (or Community Builder).
		It enables to display the feed of a Chatter Group (or a set of groups) directly within any page.</p>
		<p>All of its behaviour is configurable via simple App Builder configuration attributes.</p>
<pre>&lt;PEG_ChatterGroups_CMP
    title="My Chatter Feed"
	icon="standard:groups"
	showBorder="true"
	configStr='["Group Name A","Group Name B"]'/&gt;</pre>
        <p>Notes:</p>
        <ul>
        	<li>Custom labels may be in title (via <code>$Label.c.CustomLabelName</code> syntax).</li>
        	<li>The component relies on the
                <a href="/docs/component-library/bundle/forceChatter:publisher/documentation">
        		<code>forceChatter:publisher</code></a> standard component for feed display.</li>
		</ul>
        <br/>
	</div>

    <div class="slds-m-top_large">
	<h4>Leveraging Context Merge</h4>
		<p>The <code>&lt;c:PEG_ChatterGroups_CMP&gt;</code> component leverages the
        <a href="/docs/component-library/bundle/c:PEG_Merge_CMP/documentation">
        <code>PEG_Merge_CMP</code></a> component to contextualise the set of chatter 
            groups the feeds of which to display in the component.</p>
        <p>Typical use case is to asapt the set of chatter groups made available
        per user, using the {{{User.xxx}}} merge token.</p>
        
        <p>It may be used to specify a specific Chatter Group name (leveraging
        a custom User text field providing this value), as in</p>
<pre>&lt;c:PEG_ChatterGroups_CMP
    title="My Chatter Feed"
    icon="standard:groups"
    showBorder="true"
    configStr='["Group Name A","{{{User.MainChatterGroup__c}}}"]'/&gt;</pre>
        <p>with <code>MainChatterGroup__c</code> having a value like
        <code>TEST Chatter Group</code>.</p>
  
        <p>It may be used to specify the whole list (leveraging a custom User
        text field providing this value), as in </p>
<pre>&lt;c:PEG_ChatterGroups_CMP
	icon="standard:groups"
	showBorder="true"
	configStr='{{{User.ChatterGroupList__c}}}'/&gt;</pre>
        <p>with <code>ChatterGroupList__c</code> having a value like
        <code>["TEST Chatter Group 1","TEST Chatter Group 2"]</code>.</p>
		<br/>
	</div>
        
